    "from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import proj3d\n",
    "def plot_hstate_modes(mdl, el_size=10, id_size=30, nom_size=50, el_alpha=1.0, mdl_range=[],\n",
    "                      range_alpha=1.0, range_size=10, title = \"Space of Fault Modes\", colors=[\"yellow\", \"orange\", \"red\", \"blue\"]):\n",
    "    x= [hstates.get('friction', 0.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "    y= [hstates.get('transfer', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "    z= [hstates.get('drift', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    x_id= [hstates.get('friction', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items() if mode[:5]!='hmode']\n",
    "    y_id= [hstates.get('transfer', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items() if mode[:5]!='hmode']\n",
    "    z_id= [hstates.get('drift', 0.0) for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items() if mode[:5]!='hmode']\n",
    "    id_labels= [mode for mode, hstates in mdl.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items() if mode[:5]!='hmode']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    fig = plt.figure()\n",
    "    fig.patch.set_alpha(0.7)\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax = fig.add_subplot(projection='3d')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if mdl_range:\n",
    "        x_r= [hstates.get('friction', 0.0) for mode, hstates in mdl_range.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "        y_r= [hstates.get('transfer', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl_range.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "        z_r= [hstates.get('drift', 1.0) for mode, hstates in mdl_range.fxns['drive'].m.mode_state_dict.items()  if mode[:5]=='hmode']\n",
    "        ax.scatter(x_r, y_r, z_r, label='range', color=colors[0], s=range_size, alpha=range_alpha)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ax.scatter(x, y, z, label='set', color=colors[1], s=el_size, alpha=el_alpha)\n",
    "    ax.scatter(x_id, y_id, z_id, label='identified', marker='X', color=colors[2], s=id_size, alpha=0.8)\n",
    "    ax.scatter([1.0], [1.0], [0.0], label='nominal', marker='*', color=colors[3], s=nom_size)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    proj=ax.get_tightbbox(fig.canvas.get_renderer())\n",
    "    \n",
    "    ax2 = fig.add_subplot()\n",
    "    ax2.patch.set_alpha(0.0)\n",
    "    xmin, _, _ = proj3d.proj_transform(ax.get_xlim()[0], ax.get_ylim()[0], 0,  ax.get_proj())\n",
    "    xmax, _, _ = proj3d.proj_transform(ax.get_xlim()[1], ax.get_ylim()[1], 0,  ax.get_proj())\n",
    "    _, ymin, _ = proj3d.proj_transform(ax.get_xlim()[1], ax.get_ylim()[0], 0,  ax.get_proj())\n",
    "    _, ymax, _ = proj3d.proj_transform(ax.get_xlim()[0], ax.get_ylim()[1], 0,  ax.get_proj())\n",
    "    ylims = proj3d.proj_transform(ax.get_xlim()[0], ax.get_ylim()[1], 1,  ax.get_proj())\n",
    "    ax2.set_xlim(xmin, xmax)\n",
    "    ax2.set_ylim(ymin-0.01, ymax+0.01)\n",
    "    ax2.set_position((0.30, 0.3, 0.42, 0.4)) \n",
    "    plt.axis('off')\n",
    "    #ax2.get_xaxis().set_visible(False)\n",
    "    #ax2.get_yaxis().set_visible(False)\n",
    "    for i, label in enumerate(id_labels):\n",
    "        #ax.text(x_id[i], y_id[i], z_id[i], label, ha='left', va='bottom')\n",
    "        xlab, ylab, _ = proj3d.proj_transform(x_id[i], y_id[i], z_id[i],  ax.get_proj())\n",
    "        if label=='stuck_left': xyt=(-20,-30)\n",
    "        elif label=='stuck': xyt=(20,-30)\n",
    "        else: xyt=(20,30)\n",
    "        plt.annotate(label, xy=(xlab, ylab), xytext=xyt, \n",
    "            textcoords='offset points', ha='center', va='bottom',\n",
    "            bbox=dict(boxstyle='round,pad=0.2', fc='white', alpha=1.0),\n",
    "            arrowprops=dict(arrowstyle='-|>', color=colors[2]))\n",
    "        #ax2.text(xlab, ylab, label, ha='left', va='bottom')\n",
    "    ax.set_title(title)\n",
    "\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('friction')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('transfer')\n",
    "    ax.set_zlabel('drift')\n",
    "    ax.legend()\n",
    "    handles, labels = ax.get_legend_handles_labels()\n",
    "    ax.get_legend().remove()\n",
    "    ax2.legend(handles, labels, loc=(0.3,-0.2), framealpha=0.55, facecolor='white')\n",
    "    ax2.get_legend().legendHandles[0]._sizes = [20]\n",
    "    return fig"
   ]

   "source": [
    "Below we look at how this results in different potential analyses...\n",
    "\n",
    "This function plots the end distribution of a given attribue from the model endclasses."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_enddist(endclasses, att='end_dist', range=(0,3), endclasses_range=[], density=False, yscale=\"log\", \n",
    "                 fail_thresh=1.0, thresh_label=\"Off Course\", x_lab=\"Line Distance\", n_bins = 8,\n",
    "                 title=\"Results Distributions Given From Approaches\", colors=[\"yellow\", \"orange\", \"red\"],\n",
    "                hatching = ['xx', '//', '..']):\n",
    "    if endclasses_range:\n",
    "        x_range_class = [endclass for scen, endclass in endclasses_range.get_values(att).items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']\n",
    "        n,bins,patches = plt.hist(x_range_class, density=density, label='range', range=range, color=colors[0], \n",
    "                                  hatch=hatching[0], bins=n_bins, edgecolor=\"white\")\n",
    "        x_elaborated_class = [endclass for scen, endclass in endclasses.get_values(att).items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']\n",
    "        n,bins,patches = plt.hist(x_elaborated_class, density=density, alpha=0.8, label='set', range=range, bins=bins,\n",
    "                                  color=colors[1], hatch=hatching[1], edgecolor=\"white\")\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        x_elaborated_class = [endclass for scen, endclass in endclasses.get_values(att).items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']\n",
    "        n,bins,patches = plt.hist(x_elaborated_class, density=density, label='set', range=range, \n",
    "                                  color=colors[1], hatch=hatching[1], bins=n_bins, edgecolor=\"white\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if fail_thresh: plt.axvline(fail_thresh, label=thresh_label, color=\"black\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    x_identified_class = [endclass for scen, endclass in endclasses.get_values(att).items() if scen[6:11]!='hmode' and scen[0:6]!='nominal']\n",
    "    label_identified_class = [scen[6:] for scen, endclass in endclasses.get_values(att).items() if scen[6:11]!='hmode'and scen[0:6]!='nominal']\n",
    "    \n",
    "    _,_,_ = plt.hist(x_identified_class, density=density, alpha=0.8, bins=bins, label='identified', color=colors[2], hatch=hatching[2], edgecolor=\"white\")\n",
    "    plt.grid(axis='y', which='both', zorder=0)\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "    plt.yscale(yscale)\n",
    "    if yscale==\"log\": plt.ylabel(\"# of Scens (log)\")\n",
    "    else:             plt.ylabel(\"Distribution\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(x_lab)\n",
    "    plt.xlim(range)\n",
    "    plt.title(title)\n",
    "    return plt.gcf()"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cluster Analysis\n",
    "\n",
    "Below, we use clustering to identify similar sets of synthetic modes."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# import pip\n",
    "# pip install scikit-learn"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.cluster import DBSCAN as cluster #DBSCAN\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_X (mdlhists, hmode = True):\n",
    "    if hmode:\n",
    "        x = np.array([[value[-1]] for scen, value in mdlhists.get_values('flows.pos.s.x').items() if 'hmode' in scen])\n",
    "        y = np.array([[value[-1]] for scen, value in mdlhists.get_values('flows.pos.s.y').items() if 'hmode' in scen])\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        x = np.array([[value[-1]] for scen, value in mdlhists.get_values('flows.pos.s.x').items() if 'hmode' not in scen])\n",
    "        y = np.array([[value[-1]] for scen, value in mdlhists.get_values('flows.pos.s.y').items() if 'hmode' not in scen])\n",
    "    return np.concatenate((x, y), axis=1)\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To find similar trajectories, we will cluster on the x-y coordinates of the end position of the Rover accross these scenarios:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 26,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_range = get_X (mdlhists_range)\n",
    "ec_range = [endclass for scen, endclass in results_range.get_values('end_dist').items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_set = get_X (mdlhists_set)\n",
    "ec_set = [endclass for scen, endclass in results_set.get_values('end_dist').items() if scen[6:11]=='hmode']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 28,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_id = get_X (mdlhists_set, hmode = False)\n",
    "ec_id = [endclass for scen, endclass in results_set.get_values('end_dist').items() if scen[6:11]!='hmode' and scen[0:6]!='nominal']\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To identify where all the clusters are accross all three approaches, we first have to combine the three sets of data into one (otherwise it might cluster differently)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 29,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X = np.concatenate((X_range, X_set, X_id))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This runs the clustering algorithm:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 30,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cl = cluster().fit(X)\n",
    "labels = cl.labels_"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},

   ],
   "source": [
    "unique_labels = set(labels)\n",
    "len(unique_labels)- (1 if -1 in labels else 0)"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "source": [
    "This function categorizes the results of each approach into the given clusters"

   "cell_type": "code",

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_cats(categorizations, X, ec, unique_categorizations):\n",
    "    cats={}\n",
    "    for cat in unique_categorizations:\n",
    "        cats[cat] = [ec[i] for i,x in enumerate(X) if categorizations[tuple(x)]==cat]+[0]\n",
    "    return cats"
   ]

   "cell_type": "code",

    "cats = get_cats(categorizations,X_range, ec_range, unique_labels)"

  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 42,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def worst_cat(categorizations, X, ec, unique_categorizations):\n",
    "    worst_cats={}\n",
    "    for cat in unique_categorizations:\n",
    "        cats = [ec[i] for i,x in enumerate(X) if categorizations[tuple(x)]==cat]+[0]\n",
    "        worst_cats[cat] = np.max(cats)\n",
    "    return worst_cats"
   ]

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Finally, we use the following to calculate more detailed statistics about the cluster coverage."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 52,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin, xmax, ymin, ymax, xs, ys):\n",
    "    return calc_coverage_loss(xmin, xmax, xs)*calc_coverage_loss(ymin, ymax, ys)\n",
    "def calc_coverage_loss(xmin, xmax, xs):\n",
    "    if xs:\n",
    "        return (xmax-np.max(xs)+np.min(xs)-xmin)/(xmax-xmin)\n",
    "    else: \n",
    "        return  (xmax-xmin)/(xmax-xmin)\n",
    "def get_xs_ys(values, X_type):\n",
    "    return [v[0] for v in values if v in X_type], [v[1] for v in values if v in X_type]"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 53,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "cov_loss_id,cov_loss_set,cov_loss_range = [],[],[]\n",
    "num_scens_id,num_scens_set,num_scens_range = [],[],[]\n",
    "for cat, values in cat_values.items():\n",
    "    xs = [v[0] for v in values]\n",
    "    ys = [v[1] for v in values]\n",
    "    xs_id, ys_id = get_xs_ys(values, X_id)\n",
    "    xs_set, ys_set = get_xs_ys(values, X_set)\n",
    "    xs_range, ys_range = get_xs_ys(values, X_range)\n",
    "    xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax = np.min(xs), np.max(xs), np.min(ys), np.max(ys)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    cov_loss_id.append(calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax ,xs_id,ys_id))\n",
    "    cov_loss_set.append(calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax ,xs_set,ys_set))\n",
    "    cov_loss_range.append(calc_2d_cov_loss(xmin,xmax,ymin,ymax, xs_range,ys_range))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    num_scens_id.append(len(xs_id));num_scens_set.append(len(xs_set));num_scens_range.append(len(xs_range))"
   ]
  },
